# Documentation source policy
- Use **Context7** for documentation-backed answers when the topic is library/tool/framework documentation.
- Match **existing patterns** in the repo (naming, CTE structure, materializations, folder layout) before introducing a new style.

# Kimball / dimensional modeling (summary)
- State the **grain** of every mart fact/dimension explicitly (one row = …).
- Prefer **conformed dimensions** and consistent natural keys across facts; align surrogate keys with existing `dim_*` / `fct_*` patterns in the repo.
- Facts should be **atomic** at the declared grain; avoid hidden many-to-many fan-out—resolve in staging/intermediate with clear dedupe or aggregation.
- Document **role-playing dimensions**, **degenerate dimensions**, and **SCD** behaviour in YAML/docs when you introduce or change them.
- For project-specific standards (naming, versioning, post-hooks), follow **in-repo docs and existing dimensional models**; do not contradict established patterns.

